==Italian==
===Etymology===
Latin ''[[qualis]]''
===Adjective===
'''quale''' ''m and f'' (''plural'' '''[[quali]]'''; ''poetic or archaic, before consonant'' quai, qua')

#(''in a question'') [[what]]?
#:'''''Quale''' uomo era?'' - what man was it?
#(''in choosing options'') [[which]]?
#:'''''Quale''' macchina preferisci?'' - Which car do you prefer?
#(''in an exclamation'') [[what]]
#:'''''Quale''' fortuna!'' - What luck!

====Synonyms====
*(''in a question''): [[che]]
*(''in an exclamation''): [[che]]

===Interrogative pronoun===
'''quale'''

#[[which]] ... ?
#* '''Quale''' dei tre é il più grande? - Which of the three is biggest?

===Relative pronoun===
'''il quale''' ''m'' (''f'' '''la quale''', ''m plural'' '''i quali''', ''f plural'' '''le quali''')

#(''referring to a person'') [[who]]
#:''Mia moglie, la '''quale''' é bella'' - My wife, who is beautiful
#(''referring to a thing'') [[which]], [[that]]
#:''La mia macchina, la '''quale''' é vecchia'' - My car, which is old
#(''preceded by a preposition'') to [[whom]]
#:''L'uomo con il '''quale''' parlo'' - The man to whom I speak
#(''in lists'') [[such as]], [[like]]
#:''Verdura '''quali''' le carote ed i piselli'' - Vegetables such as carrots and peas

====Synonyms====
